lines.text: Whoa! It's raining cats and dogs out there!
I hope they make it back alright.
Don't forget to wash your hands!
Jessie. Buzz. Slink. Molly's room. The rest of you, stay put.
Billy. Goat. Gruff. Raise the blinds.
They have names? You never told me that.
I ain't got any more slink!
I'm so glad to see this old lamp go to a good home. We've had it since Molly was a baby.
Molly, are you sure it's alright?
Yeah, I don't want it anymore.
Yeah, hi. I think I left my keys here.
Quick! We'll sneak in the hedges before he's back.
What? No! No, no, no. You can't go! What's best for Andy is that...
It's time for the next kid.
Oh, and thank you again for everything. I really appreciate it.
Oh, my pleasure. I'm glad it all worked out.
You know, kids lose their toys every day. Sometimes they get left in the yard, or put in the wrong box.
And that box gets taken away.
Mom, I found him! I found him!
Oh, good. Come on and get inside.
There's a snake in my boot!
They've escaped and they're headed right for us!
Ugh! It's getting hot in here!
Could you move over a bit, please?
I know that was you, Potato Head.
Everyone, listen. I thought I told you, when Mom quickly cleans the bedroom like that, expect to be put in the closet.
Keep it to a dull roar, Rex. Deep breaths, Jessie, deep breaths. Settle down, Slink. Sit. Good boy!
Sheriff, do I need to be worried?
No, no. My guys are veterans. They'll hang in there.
Good. Just keep 'em calm until we get word.
How are you, uh, feeling about today?
Uh, good, good. Yeah, good. I'm good.
We're on! Bonnie's done with breakfast! Any minute now.
You hear that? Any minute now. Wind 'em if you've got 'em! Keep your batteries clean, your joints unlocked...
Uh, thanks, Woody. I've got it.
Yes, I'm sorry. You're right, you're right.
The town is open! Hi, Mayor! Banker! Hi, Ice Cream Man! Hi, Hat Shop Owner! Mailman! And the Sheriff! Okay, bye toys!
They went that way! Chase them!
What a beautiful hat shop! You have so many hats...
When's the last time we ever got to play that?
It was basic. You built a house, you lived in it, done.
Hmm. That's the third time you haven't been picked this week.
I don't know. I don't keep count.
Oh, you don't have to. I'll do it for you.
Okay, okay, okay, I get it. It's been a while.
Oh, looky there! You got your first dust bunny!
Aw, how adorable. What you gonna name it?
Well, he's a cowboy, so that makes a lot of sense.
So many choices. I just can't decide!
Bonnie? What are you doing? We've gotta go. You don't wanna be late for kindergarten orientation, do you?
We talked about this. We're gonna meet your teachers, see your classroom...
Toys don't go to school, that, that's the rule.
Nobody move! Bonnie always forgets something. She'll be back any second.
That goes for you too, Hamm.
You all right, Woody? I'm sure she'll pick you next time.
Oh, come on, I'm fine. No problem.
I don't want to play the baker.
The hat shop owner is the role I was born to play!
Ok. Right, All right, Pricklepants, back to your bakery.
Woody, can't you see I'm threatening everyone? Go back to the closet.
Yeah, I know, I know. It's just... I'm worried about Bonnie. A toy should go with her to orientation.
Didn't you hear Dad? You'll get Bonnie in trouble.
Yeah, but kindergarten is so different. It can be too much for a kid. Having a buddy with them to get through it can really help things. I remember with Andy, I would go to school with him...
Uh-huh. I'm sorry, Woody, I hate to sound like a broken record, but Bonnie's not Andy.
No, no, no, of course, I get that. But if you would just hear me out...
What are you doing back there? C'mon, we have to go.
Come on. We gotta hurry, ok? Don't forget your backpack.
You're gonna have so much fun.
All right, now what was it you were saying Woody?
Hi! Are you Bonnie? My name is Miss Wendy. I'm going to be your kindergarten teacher!
We have a special place where you can put your backpack.
Okay, class, let's all find a seat at a table, so we can start craft time.
Oh, Bonnie. That is so clever.
Hello, I'm Forky. Nice to meet you!
Why, hello, Forky, it's nice to meet you. I'm Miss Wendy.
Mom! Dad! Look what I made!
Uh... no. That- That- That was just orientation.
But for being such a brave girl, we have a surprise for you.
Since school doesn't start for another week, we are going on a road trip!
And they said I shouldn't go to school with Bonnie.
We got this whole Kindergarten thing under control, eh?
I can't believe I'm talking to a spork.
You tryin' to get Bonnie in trouble?
Or worse. You could have been lost!
No, no, no, guys, listen. Bonnie had a great day in class, and we're going on a road trip.
But then something really weird thing happened. Bonnie made a friend in class.
No, no. She literally made a new friend.
Hey, it's okay. Come on out.
That's it. Come on, there you go.
Come on, let's get you out of there.
You got this. Good. Good. Everyone, I want you to meet Forky.
Look how long his arms are!
No. No, toys. They're all toys.
No, no, no. That's the trash. These are your friends.
Shh, shh, no, no it's okay.
Woody, I have a question. Um, well, actually, not just one, I have all of them. I have all the questions.
Uh, why does he want to go to the trash?
Because he was made from trash.
Look, I know this is a little strange, but you got to trust me on this.
Forky is THE most important toy to Bonnie right now.
Yes. Yeah, I know, but this spork-- this toy is crucial to Bonnie getting adjusted to kindergarten.
Woody, aren't you being a little dramatic about all of this?

I know this is new to everybody, but you should see how much this little guy means to Bonnie. When she started playing with him, she had the biggest smile on her face. I wish you could have seen it. Bonnie was really upset, and I swear, once she made Forky, it as a complete transformation.
Just a second, Jessie. So, we all have to make sure nothing happens to him.
No, no, no! No, no, no! You're a toy now, Forky! Come on! Stop! Stop it! Hey! No, no, no! Come on!
Well, I guess I'll babysit him till he's used to the room.
There you are! I thought I'd lost you, silly.
No, no, no, no, no. Big girl scary!
Like I said before, Bonnie's not scary. She loves you and you need to...
Me! I'm gonna bring Dolly and Buttercup and Forky and...
Come on. let's eat some breakfast and hit the road!
Whoa. He's quite a handful, Woody. You need help with him on the road trip?
No. No, no. I got it, I got it.
We'll just be stuck in an RV. He can't get far. I got this. I got it.
I don't wanna be a toy!
I don't know, Buzz. I know you weren't around when Andy was little , but I don't remember it being this hard.
Want me to take the next watch? I'll keep an eye on Forky.
No, no. I need to do this. That little voice inside me would never leave me alone if I gave up.
Huh. Who do you think it is?
The voice inside of you. Who do you think it is?
The part of you that tells you things? What you're really thinking?
Fascinating. So, your inner voice advises you.
It's a secret mission in uncharted space! Let's go!
I am not a toy! I'm a spork.
I was made for soup, salad, maybe chili, and then the trash.
Hamm, how far to our next stop?
I'll meet you at the RV park.
Forky! Forky, where are you? Forky! Forky, where are you?
Why do I have to be a toy?
Because you have Bonnie's name written on the bottom of your sticks.
Why do I have Bonnie's name written on the bottom of my sticks?
Look, she plays with you all the time, right?
And who does she sleep with every night?
All right, Forky. You have to understand how lucky you are right now. You're Bonnie's toy. You are going to help create happy memories that will last for the rest of her life!
Okay. Doing it for Bonnie. Doing this for Bonnie, you're doing it for Bonnie.
Okay, like it or not, you are A toy . Maybe you don't like being one, but you are one nonetheless. Which means you are going to be there for Andy when he...
I mean, Bonnie. You have to be there for Bonnie. That is your job.
Well, right now, it's to make sure you do yours.
Yeah, yeah. For a long time. And it was pretty great. I was a favorite toy, actually. Running the room was my job. Keeping all the toys in place...
Well, right now, it's to make sure you do yours.
Yeah, yeah. For a long time. And it was pretty great. I was a favorite toy, actually. Running the room was my job. Keeping all the toys in place...
So, he thought Andy's room was a planet? Wow, that is messed up.
Right! That's exactly what I thought when he first showed up.
Yeah. I mean, how is that not annoying?

Well, then you watch 'em grow up and become a full person. And then they leave. They go off and do things you'll never see. Don't get me wrong, you still feel good about it. But then somehow you find yourself, after all those years... sitting in a closet just feeling...
Woody, I know what your problem is.
What is it with you and trash?
And safe! Like somebody's whispering in your ear, "Everything's gonna be okay."
Forky, that's it. That's how Bonnie feels when she's with you.
Wait a sec. You mean she thinks I'm warm?
I get it now. I'm Bonnie's trash.
Oh, she must be feeling awful without me. Woody, we've gotta get going, she needs me!
Hey, Bonnie, I'm coming! Come on, Woody! Bonnie, I'm coming! Ooh-hoo-hoo-hoo!
Whoa, Whoa! Forky, slow down! Forky! Forky!
Forky, look. Bonnie's right over there.
Woody? Aren't we-- Aren't we going to Bonnie?
I know, I know. But my friend might be in there.
Oh, a friend, uh... Well, a friend is... Well, a friend is like you and me.
Trash, like... Yes. And I'm very worried that she might be lost.
Yeah. Yeah. We'll have you back before she wakes up. Come on.
Bo Bo Bo Bo Bo, Bo- Can we go back to Bonnie now? I don't see your friend.
Yeah, okay. She's not in here. Come on, let's go.
Uh... Hey, howdy. Hey there. Uh, sorry to bother you, but...
Why, you're not a bother at all.
We were just out for my early morning stroll. And look! Ha-ha! We met you! My name is Gabby Gabby. And this is my very good friend Benson.
Oh, uh, Woody. Pleasure to meet you.
Well, it's nice to meet you, Woody. And you are...?
Kid? Toys around here don't have kids. Are you two lost?
Lost? No, no. But we are looking for a lost toy. She's a figurine. Used to be on that lamp in the window? Name's Bo Peep?
Bo Peep? Oh, yes, I know Bo.
Hop on in. We'll take you to her.
Oh um, you don't have to that. Well, okay.
Benson, be careful with our new friends.
Uh... Thank you for your help. I haven't seen Bo in years.
May I ask, when were you made?
Me? Uh... I'm not sure. Late 50's?
Me, too! Gee, I wonder if we were made in the same factory. Wouldn't that be something? I gotta say, you are in great condition.
Well, I try to stay active.
And look at that, you have a voice box like me. Benson, show him.
Oh, oh, that's- that's really not necessary.
I'm Gabby Gabby, and I love you.
Wow, you need to fix that.
My record works just fine. It's the voice box that's broken. Does yours still work?
There's a snake in my boot!
Listen to that! Let's see it. I bet it's the same type.
Oh, no, no, no thanks, mine's sewn inside. Is Bo around here because we need...
Oh. The store is about to open. Don't worry, we'll take you where no one will see us.
Oh, oh, no. We can't stay.
You can't leave yet. You have what I need. Right inside there.
Returned that lamp the next day.
Mom, can we go to the park now?
What's going on? Come on! Let's go! He's coming, he's coming! I see him!
I'd like to join your posse boys, but first I'm gonna sing a little song.
Grandma, look what I found. Can I take it to the park?
Mom, she has enough toys from the store.
Oh, it's fine. Nobody buys the toys anyway.
Mom, can we go to the carnival?
We're going to the park. Maybe later, sweetie.
Maybe we should have gone with the fork.
I can't find Forky! He's missing!
Oh, Bonnie, it'll be all right. I'm sure he's here somewhere. You know, if you don't find him, you can make a new one.
Uh... Let's go look outside. Maybe he fell on the ground somewhere.
We have to find him, Mom. He needs me.
Woody was right. We all should have been safeguarding the utensil.
Buzz, what do we do? What do we do, Buzz? What do we do, Buzz? Buzz! Buzz.
Eh, jump out of a moving vehicle?
It's a secret mission in uncharted space. Let's go!
I think I have to go.
Should we all go? Are we going?
Okay, what is with everyone jumping out the window?
Woody and Forky were last seen on the highway. But where is the highway?
The slingshot maneuver is all we've got! Full speed ahead!
The highway. On my way, Woody!
Hey! Step right up! Put your money down! Get yourself a real Buzz Lightyear! Hey! Hey!
Okay. Be right back, mister cowboy.
Did you see 'em? How many are there?
We got a busload of campers!
Oh, baby! It's a good day to play, huh? Am I right?
Hello, Mr. Cowboy. How are you today? Do you like riding horses?
Oh, I can't believe it's you!!
I never thought I'd see you again!!
Oh, I can't believe it's you!!
I never thought I'd see you again!!
Wait, you're- you're a lost toy?
I mean awfully great that you are lost out here.
I told you not to drive so fast. You almost ran him over.
Oh, hey, guys! Whoa! Whoa! Hold on there! Okay! I missed you, too. If it isn't Bobby?
Okay, let's get a look at you. You need any repairs?
Where did you get all this stuff?
Here and there. You know, some kids play rougher than others, so I try to be prepared.
How long have you been out on your own?
You would not believe the things I've seen.
Come on out! There's someone I want you to meet.
What's the situation? We heading out of town or...
You remember the rag doll I told you about?
Whoa, you didn't tell me he was a cop.
Howdy, Sheriff. Officer Giggle McDimples. I run Pet Patrol from Mini-Opolis. Yeah, search and rescue. Ants, caterpillars, miniature poodles, spiders.
Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut!
Combat Carl just heard there's a birthday party at the playground on Main Street.
Rumor has it, they got two pinatas.
Oh, yeah! Combat Carl's gettin' played with!
You bet! Woody, you are gonna love this!
sir. Bo, I need to get back to my kid.
Way to beat the odds, soldier.
Meet you at the playground, Peep. Combat Carl's got a pinata party to crash. All right, move out.
Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut! Hut!
So, you're, uh, with a kid? It's not Andy, is it?
He went off to college. But he gave us to Bonnie.
Yeah, yeah. It's why I'm out here. Her other toy is trapped in this antique store,
Second Chance Antiques? We know that store.
That's great. That is great! If you know the store, you could really help me find him...
No way. We wasted years there, just sitting on the shelf, collecting dust.
Oh, Bo, that's awful. But I don't have a choice. I have to get that toy from Gabby.
Woah. Steer clear of that weirdo.
If I were you, I'd cut my losses and go home.
But Bonnie needs him to get through kindergarten.
Oh, kids lose toys every day. Bonnie will get over it.
No, no, but... you see... Bonnie needs him just like... Molly needed you.
Aw, no. Sorry, girls. Molly's not here.
Molly? Bo, I didn't know you had a kid.
That was a long time ago.
Oh, Bo's kid was something special. She was the cutest thing, but so afraid of the dark.

Oh, you weren't there in the beginning. Hearing Molly cry each night, it broke every toy's heart. And then, Bo came into the room. Her lamp was the only thing that made Molly feel safe. Mom would let her keep Bo on all night.
Ha! Who knew you were such a softy?
And Molly would fall asleep with her hand resting on Bo's feet.
Bo, my kid really needs this toy. Will you help me? For old times sake.
Thank you! Oh! Oh, thank you!
All right. Guess we're doing this.
Second Chance Antiques, and step on it.
Look at that! Good as new.
Uh, so um, when's Woody coming back?
Like I said, soon. He won't forget about you.
You have your child's name written on your feet... Sticks. That makes you a very important toy.
Wait a second, she took Woody.
Forky, it's tea time. It's tea time.
A little bit of milk, two lumps of sugar.
I've been practicing. How do I look?
Harmony, sweetie, I'm leaving. Come give me a hug.
When my voice box is fixed, I'll finally get my chance.
I wanna know everything about him.

Oh, yeah, Woody. I've known that guy my whole life. Two days! Hey, did you know that Bonnie was not his first kid? He had this other kid, Andy. And you know what? I don't think he's ever gotten over him.
If you think you can just show up and take our top prize spot, you're wrong!
You don't understand. I'm trying to...
Cheat the system and get with a kid? Yeah, we know.
A child to shower you with unconditional love? Join the club, pal.
Come on, help me get out of here.
Oh, I'll help you. With my foot!
I-I can't reach him. Help me out here, come on.
Oh. Sorry, Ducky. I'm not a mind reader, you know.
You gonna make me say it?
With these tiny legs, I cannot reach without your help.
This is what I've been talking about, Bunny. You need to work on your attention and your listening skills.
How you like that, cheater? Huh?
Yeah! Ha-ha! Oh, oh, to infinity and my foot!
In a galaxy far, far away, you got kicked in the head!
How do I get out of here?
This planet is toxic. Closing helmet to conserve oxygen.
In the vacuum of space, they cannot hear you-
Hey. What am I doing? Why would Ducky hurt a space ranger like that? Oh well, by the lord of a Cowboy Loving Bunny, i should be getting out of this shit.
Oh, yeah. This feels so good. Now, time to fly! [Jumps off]
Oh, yeah! This feels so good. Now, time to unfreeze.
Wait, youre the space ranger of the galactic world of time?!
Ooh! So that's what gravity feel like.
You better take a look at this.
You better get over here, Bunny!
Yeah, dont leave us right there!
Buzz, what are you doing? He's getting away, let's go!
Bo, why do you ride around in a skunk?
Corn dogs, corn dogs, corn dogs,-
Come on, Woody. Its gonna be okay.
Yeah. It is. You know what? Lets keep asking each other, until we think of something.
Why are you so bad at driving? You got six eyes.
Whoa. We actually did that. Oh, yeah. Yes!
Sir, will you please step out of the vehicle?
Everyone, topside. Let's move. Forky, I've got a very important job for you.
Have a good night. What the...? You've gotta be kidding me.
Billy, Goat, Gruff. Take care of her, girls.
I'm glad I got to see you again.
Hey. Listen to your inner voice.
Oh, my goodness. The awning. What is going on?
Does this mean Woody's a lost toy?
You Mr. Toads wanna take a wild ride with a kid?
Oh, yeah! Leave it to us, Jeremiah.
We know exactly what to do.
How you like that, huh? You got plush-rushed, son! Dance! Dance! Get those knees up! Let's see those feet move! Whoo!
Or we can get more toys to kids.
Do you really have laser eyes?
What's first grade like? Tell me everything!
Uh, you mean "Show and Tell" there, big guy.
You see any kids eat paste?
Guys, listen! Bonnie had a great day in first grade. She even made a new friend in class.
No, no, she made a new friend. Come on out, it's okay.
No, no. Toy. I am a... We are all toys. Unique, beautiful toys. I will explain everything.
